subject: Re: [junit] What is difference between textual test runner and  graphical test runner?
msgSnippet: The difference is how you are presented with results.  The textual test runner displays your test results in text only.  The graphical test runner is a bit
messageBody:
The difference is how you are presented with results. The textual test
runner displays your test results in text only. The graphical test
runner is a bit nicer to look at, displaying green if all the tests
passed, and red if any one failed.

-Brian
